TITLE: Google loses massive antitrust case over its search dominance
SUMMARY: Various Google logos are displayed on a Google search on Sept. 11, 2023, in New York. U.S. District Judge Amit Mehta ruled Monday that Google's ubiquitous search engine has been illegally exploiting its dominance to squash competition and stifle innovation in a seismic decision that could shake up the internet and hobble one of the world's best-known companies

TITLE: Deb Haaland’s push to protect Indigenous people disappoints some Native leaders
SUMMARY: Laguna Pueblo citizen Deb Haaland is the U.S. Interior secretary, and the only Native American to hold a Cabinet post

TITLE: Former Trump attorney agrees to cooperation agreement in Arizona 'fake elector' case
SUMMARY: Former Trump attorney Jenna Ellis reads a statement after pleading guilty in Atlanta on Oct. 24, 2023, to one felony count of aiding and abetting false statements and writings in the Fulton County election subversion case. John Bazemore/Pool/AFP via Getty Images

TITLE: In the face of global warming, students are dreaming up a better climate future
SUMMARY: Bloomington High School South science teacher Kirstin Milks leads a lesson on human-caused climate change and technologies that could help reduce greenhouse gas emissions

TITLE: She was severely injured in a crash. A truck driver became her 'highway angel'
SUMMARY: A highway crash had both a positive and negative impact on Frances Brissey

TITLE: RFK Jr. admits to dumping a dead bear in Central Park, solving a decade-old mystery
SUMMARY: Independent presidential candidate Robert F. Kennedy Jr., pictured in May, released a video over the weekend recounting a 2014 incident in which he dumped a dead bear cub in Central Park to make it look like it had been in a bike crash

TITLE: Supreme Court rejects Missouri's bid to halt Trump’s sentencing in N.Y. hush money case
SUMMARY: The Supreme Court rejected Missouri’s attempts to halt former President Donald Trump’s sentencing and gag order in his New York hush money case. Kevin Dietsch/Getty Images/Getty Images North America
